(2012, 160882, '2012-09-27 15:15:19', '"In the present study we have shown that: (1) in the\nhippocampal formation of the rat, nonpyramidal cells containing\ndifferent calcium binding-proteins (CaBP [calbindin] and PV [parvalbumin])\nform two distinct populations with a minor overlap confined\nto stratum oriens of the CA1 subfield, and (2) CaBP and\nCCK[cholecystokinin]-containing cells in the dentate gyrus and in the\nCA1 subfield also represent largely nonoverlapping populations,\nwhereas in stratum radiatum of CA3 a small proportion\nof the neurons contained both antigens."', 'p 374 right', 'data', NULL, NULL),
