(2262, 161052, '2012-09-27 15:15:22', '"CB [calbindin] was abundantly present\nin all the layers of the dentate gyrus (Fig. 1j): in the perikarya\nof all granular neurons in the stratum granulosum, in\nthe neuropil of the stratum moleculare, and in the axons of\ngranular neurons forming mossy fibers, which, after passing\nthrough the stratum multiforme, traveled parallel to the stratum\npyramidale of sector CA3."', 'p 91 right mid', 'data', NULL, NULL),
